text: Sophia Catherine Diagne (born 10 November 1998) is a Senegalese swimmer. She competed in the women's 50 metre backstroke at the 2019 World Aquatics Championships. In 2019, she also represented Senegal at the 2019 African Games held in Rabat, Morocco. She competed in the women's 50 metre backstroke, women's 50 metre butterfly and women's 50 metre freestyle events. ==References== Category:1998 births Category:Living people Category:Senegalese female swimmers Category:Place of birth missing (living people) Category:Competitors at the 2019 African Games Category:African Games competitors for Senegal Category:Female backstroke swimmers Category:Female butterfly swimmers Category:Female freestyle swimmers
